Giridih district''' is one of the twenty-four districts of [[Jharkhand]] [[States and territories of India|state]], [[India]], and [[Giridih]] is the administrative headquarters of this district. As of 2011 it is the third most populous district of Jharkhand (out of [[Districts of Jharkhand|24]]), after [[Ranchi district|Ranchi]] and [[Dhanbad district|Dhanbad]].<ref name="districtcensus">{{cite web | url = http://www.census2011.co.in/census/district/99-giridih.html | title = District Census 2011 | accessdate = 2011-09-30 | year = 2011 | publisher = Census2011.co.in}}</ref>

